name: Hint: Skill Tree - Sexual Technique Development
About the skill tree
note:
<SG説明:
The Skill Tree is the core system of this game. By using SP (Skill
Points), you can unlock corresponding skills. The unlockable skills
are divided into the following six categories: ①Attack (skills mainly
for attacking enemies) ②Resist (passive skills that nullify abnormal
status) ③Technical (special skills for roles other than their original
purpose) ④Unique (skills that enhance their original role) ⑤Status
(passive skills that increase basic abilities) ⑥AAA (leveling up AAA)）
>
<SG種別:3>
<SGカテゴリ:スキルツリー・性技開発>
<SG収集対象外>

name: Basic Rules of the Skill Tree
note:
<SG説明:
The skill tree has the following rules. Please acquire skills
according to your training policy. ① 1 SP is required to unlock one
skill. ② Since it is a tree, you need to acquire skills from the
bottom up. ③ Once a skill is unlocked, it cannot be forgotten. ④ Some
skills have hidden skills (sexual techniques) that are reflected in
sexual technique development. ⑤ Developing sexual techniques
strengthens corresponding skills.
>
<SG種別:3>
<SGカテゴリ:スキルツリー・性技開発>
<SG収集対象外>

name: About SP
note:
<SG説明:
SP（Skill Points (SP) are necessary for unlocking skills. SP can be
obtained through the following methods: ① Obtained through leveling
up. ② Obtained through items. Items that increase SP can be obtained
in dungeons or towns through Nora and Relm's AAA. They can also be
obtained as quest rewards.
>
<SG種別:3>
<SGカテゴリ:スキルツリー・性技開発>
<SG収集対象外>

name: About sexual technique development
note:
<SG説明:
The development of sexual techniques is the core system of this game.
By using AP (Adult Points), you can develop sexual techniques (hidden
skills). The following rules exist for the development of sexual
techniques:  1. It requires 1 AP to develop one sexual technique. 2.
By unlocking specific skills in the skill tree, corresponding sexual
techniques are also unlocked. 3. Developing sexual techniques enhances
the corresponding skills. 4. Developing sexual techniques allows you
to obtain lewd points for increasing the lewd level. 5. By developing
a certain number of sexual techniques, the lewd level increases.  As
the lewd level increases, more adult scenes become available for
viewing. Many adult scenes require a specific lewd level as a
condition for viewing. When increasing the lewd level, please make
sure you haven't missed any scenes. The number of scenes available for
viewing at the current lewd level can be confirmed on the sexual
technique development screen.
>
<SG種別:3>
<SGカテゴリ:スキルツリー・性技開発>
<SG収集対象外>

name: About Lewdness Level.
note:
<SG説明:
The Lewd Level increases based on the Lewd Value obtained through
sexual technique development. The maximum level is 4, and the maximum
number of developments is 54 times. ① The Lewd Level ranges from 1 to
4, with 4 being the maximum. ② Each development grants 2 Lewd Value. ③
To upgrade from Lewd Level 1 to Level 2, a Lewd Value of [10] is
required. ④ To upgrade from Lewd Level 2 to Level 3, a Lewd Value of
[30] is required. ⑤ To upgrade from Lewd Level 3 to Level 4, a Lewd
Value of [40] is required. ⑥ The total Lewd Value required to develop
all sexual techniques is [108]. ⑦ Once a sexual technique is
developed, it cannot be undone. ⑧ Once the Lewd Level is leveled up,
it cannot be reverted.
>
<SG種別:3>
<SGカテゴリ:スキルツリー・性技開発>
<SG収集対象外>

name: About AP
note:
<SG説明:
AP（Adult Points (AP) are necessary for the development of sexual
techniques. AP can be obtained through the following methods: 1)
Obtaining by viewing adult scenes other than game over scenes, 2)
Obtaining through items. Certain adult scenes can be repeated,
allowing you to earn AP. Additionally, it is possible to skip adult
scenes that you have already seen. Items that increase AP can be
obtained through Nora and Relm's AAA in dungeons and towns. They can
also be obtained as quest rewards.
>
<SG種別:3>
<SGカテゴリ:スキルツリー・性技開発>
<SG収集対象外>

name: Examples of Sexual Technique Development
note:
<SG説明:
For example, the process of obtaining the skill "Theology Fellow" for
the priestess Sophia is as follows: ① Use SP in the skill tree to
unlock "Theology Fellow" ② Unlock "Hidden Lust Lv.0" in the sexual
technique development screen, which is linked to "Theology Fellow" ③
Use AP to develop it into "Hidden Lust Lv.1" ④ The skill changes to
"Theology Fellow+1" and its contents are strengthened. You can check
the changes through the sexual technique development screen. The
skills after development can be confirmed in the "Skills" menu.
>
<SG種別:3>
<SGカテゴリ:スキルツリー・性技開発>
<SG収集対象外>

name: Basic Quest System
note:
<SG説明:
The quest system is the fundamental system of this game. In principle,
events occur by accepting quests. The following are the basics of the
quest system in this game. ① In order to start an event, it is
generally necessary to accept a quest. ② There are two types of
quests: guild quests and stray quests. ③ The level of the quest is
defined by the icon background color and ☆. ④ The icon background
color defines the difficulty as blue → green → red → black. ⑤ ☆
defines the difficulty on a scale of 1 to 10. ⑥\c[1]Blue\c[0]:
☆1-3\c[3]Green\c[0]: ☆4-6 \c[10] Red\c[0]: ☆7-9\c[7]Black\c[0]: ☆10 ⑦
The icon type defines the general genre of the quest. ⑧ There are
conditions for accepting quests. ⑨ There are also quests that must be
accepted forcibly. ⑩ There are repeatable quests that can be accepted
multiple times. ⑪ Accepted quests can be confirmed in the quest
report. ⑫ Available quests can be confirmed in the regional quest list
in the menu.
>

name: About Skills and Magic
note:
<SG説明:
In order to reflect the world view of the work, Clea and Nora use the
term "Skill," while Relm and Sophia use the term "Magic." ① Skills and
magic can be learned through leveling up. ② Skills and magic can be
acquired through the skill tree. ③ Some skills and magic can be
enhanced through sexual technique development. ④ There are passive
skills that cannot be directly used in combat. ⑤ There are AAA skills
that cannot be directly used in combat. ⑥ Skills and magic are
generally used by consuming MP. For more details on the skill tree,
please refer to the "Skill Tree" in the hints.
>
<SG種別:3>
<SGカテゴリ:戦闘システム>
<SG収集対象外>

name: About Special Moves and TP
note:
<SG説明:
Special moves can be learned up to a maximum of two as the story
progresses. The content of some characters' special moves changes
along with the story. Special moves can be used by consuming TP. ① TP
is reset and cannot be carried over between battles. ② The initial
value of TP is randomly allocated between 0 and 24. ③ TP increases by
taking damage, performing regular attacks, and defending. ④ TP does
not increase when using skills or magic, but there are some
exceptions. ⑤ In consecutive battles, TP cannot be carried over to the
next wave.
>
<SG種別:3>
<SGカテゴリ:戦闘システム>
<SG収集対象外>

name: About Repeat
note:
<SG説明:
The Repeat command allows you to replicate the actions of the previous
turn within the same battle. However, it is reset after each battle,
so using it on the first turn is meaningless. ① It replicates the
actions of the previous turn. ② It is reset after each battle, so
using it on the first turn is pointless. ③ If used on the first turn,
everyone will use a normal attack. ④ If it cannot replicate the
previous turn, it defaults to a normal attack (such as when out of MP
or TP).）
>
<SG種別:3>
<SGカテゴリ:戦闘システム>
<SG収集対象外>

name: About Running Away
note:
<SG説明:
In this game, it is possible to escape from battles. However, as a
cost for fleeing, you will lose a portion of your possessed gold. ①
Escaping is 100% successful. ② In certain event battles such as boss
fights, escaping is not an option. ③ When escaping, you will lose a
total of 25% of the gold that the enemy was supposed to drop. ④ After
escaping, the enemy symbols disappear and will respawn after a certain
amount of time.
>
<SG種別:3>
<SGカテゴリ:戦闘システム>
<SG収集対象外>

name: About Abnormal Status
note:
<SG説明:
The specification is such that all conditions are automatically lifted
after battles. Conditions ④, ⑤, and ⑥ have a 50% chance of being
lifted when taking damage. There are also skills in the skill tree
that can nullify abnormal statuses or prevent them for a few turns, so
please actively acquire them.
>

name: About Buffs and Debuffs
note:
<SG説明:
In this game, we have prepared skills and items that can buff and
debuff. Here is how buffs and debuffs work:  1. They can enhance or
weaken basic stats such as attack power and defense. 2. There are also
buffs and debuffs for elemental resistance and status ailment
resistance. 3. When a buff is applied, an icon will be displayed along
with the duration of the effect. 4. The effect descriptions are
categorized as small (25%), medium (50%), and large (70% or more). 5.
Buffs and debuffs with the same effect rate will cancel each other
out. 6. In the case of a 25% buff and a 50% debuff, the debuff will be
reduced to 25%. 7. When applying buffs with the same effect, only the
one with the higher effect rate will be used.
>
<SG種別:3>
<SGカテゴリ:戦闘システム>
<SG収集対象外>

name: About Buff and Debuff Icons
note:
<SG説明:
During battles, icons and turn numbers will be displayed for both
allies and enemies. Please use buffs and debuffs effectively to gain
an advantage in battle.

name: About pop-up images
note:
<SG説明:
When certain conditions are met during battle, a pop-up will be
displayed. The "Weakness" pop-up appears when you hit a weak point,
the "Guard" pop-up appears when your attacks are completely blocked by
attribute or status ailment defenses, and the "Resistance" pop-up
appears when damage is reduced due to resistance. These pop-ups
provide important information. Please make sure to carefully check the
pop-ups and proceed with the battle advantageously.

This is done to clearly indicate special situations as much as

name: About Game Over
note:
<SG説明:
When you are defeated in battle, it will result in a game over. At the
game over screen, you will be taken back to the main menu. There is no
auto-save function, so it is recommended to save regularly. Before
boss battles, there will always be an option to choose whether to
engage in battle. In the case of certain enemies that have defeat
adult scenes, it is possible to resume the battle after being
defeated. This is an exceptional behavior intended for scene recovery.
Additionally, there are also special game overs that only display
adult CG scenes.

>
<SG種別:3>

name: Character Roles
note:
<SG説明:

allies. With the skill tree unlocked, she is capable of attribute
downs and attribute attacks.  Nora - A thief who serves as a physical
attacker and debuffer. With the skill tree unlocked, she is capable of
special counters that include inflicting status ailments.  Relm - A
mage who manipulates various elemental magic as a magic attacker. With
the skill tree unlocked, she is capable of attribute enhancements and
attribute debuffs.  Sophia - A priestess who performs HP recovery and
status ailment recovery as a healer. With the skill tree unlocked, she
is capable of physical and magical attacks.

name: About Equipment Slots
note:
<SG説明:
The equipment slots are the same for all characters and are as
follows: ① [Weapon] R-Hand... weapons ② [Shield] L-Hand... bracelets ③
[Head] Head... helmets, hair ornaments, etc. ④ [Body] Body... armor,
clothing, etc. ⑤ [Accessory] Accessory... necklaces, rings, etc. The
equipment is divided into items that can be equipped by all characters
and limited items. You can check them when purchasing or on the
equipment screen.
>
<SG種別:3>
<SGカテゴリ:装備品>
<SG収集対象外>

name: About weapons
note:
<SG説明:
In this game, weapons are defined as something to be trained and
improved, rather than purchased. Therefore, there are no weapon shops,
and instead, weapon enhancement is done through blacksmithing. Weapons
can be enhanced under the blacksmith Eleo, who is located within the
adventurer's guild. By clearing required quests, you can obtain
enhancement materials. The enhancement of weapons is subject to the
following conditions: 1) Enhancement materials for the weapon, 2) Cost
for enhancement, 3) Base weapon for enhancement. Weapon enhancement
must be done in order, and it is not possible to enhance from +1 to
+3. Some enhancement materials can be obtained through optional
quests, rather than required quests. Please obtain higher-level weapon
enhancement materials through dedicated quests.
>
<SG種別:3>
<SGカテゴリ:装備品>
<SG収集対象外>

name: About Armor
note:
<SG説明:
Armor can be obtained at the town shop or through quests. The
selection at the shop increases as the adventurer rank goes up. ①
Bracelets and wristbands... can be equipped by anyone. ② Helmets and
armor... can only be equipped by Clea. ③ Hats... can be equipped by
anyone. ④ Hair ornaments... can only be equipped by Relm and Sophia. ⑤
Chest plates... can only be equipped by Clea and Nora. ⑥ Clothes...
can be equipped by anyone. ⑦ Robes... can only be equipped by Relm and
Sophia. ⑧ Accessories... can be equipped by anyone. Some armor have
skills or magic that can be used when equipped. This is always set for
cosplay costumes.
>

<SGカテゴリ:装備品>

name: About cosplay costumes
note:
<SG説明:
Cosplay costumes can be obtained through quests. By equipping them,
you can enjoy the following benefits: ① Changes in stats (same as
regular armor) ② Changes in character illustrations (during
conversations, menus, battles, and skill screens) ③ Access to hidden
skills and magic. Cosplay costumes often have unique settings, so make
sure to understand their performance and use them to your advantage in
battles.
>
<SG種別:3>
<SGカテゴリ:装備品>
<SG収集対象外>

name: About the tavern and inn.
note:
<SG説明:
Various towns have taverns and inns set up. Inns allow you to rest and
recover HP and MP by staying overnight. The main cities, excluding
Fotizona, Kanonas, and Myukos, have bulletin boards in their taverns.
Through these bulletin boards, you can accept stray quests.
Additionally, many AAA target NPCs for each character are located in
the taverns. If you discover a new town, it is recommended to first
visit the tavern.
>
<SG種別:3>
<SGカテゴリ:施設>
<SG収集対象外>

name: About the blacksmith
note:
<SG説明:
In this game, weapons are defined as something to be trained and
improved, rather than purchased. Therefore, there are no weapon shops,
and instead, weapon enhancement is done through blacksmithing. Weapons
can be enhanced under the blacksmith Eleo, who is located within the
adventurer's guild. By clearing essential quests, you can obtain
enhancement materials. The enhancement of weapons is subject to the
following conditions: 1) Enhancement materials for the weapon, 2) Cost
for enhancement, 3) Base weapon for enhancement. Weapon enhancement
must be done in order, and it is not possible to enhance from +1 to
+3. Some enhancement materials can be obtained through optional
quests, rather than essential quests. Please obtain higher-level
weapon enhancement materials through dedicated quests.
>
<SG種別:3>
<SGカテゴリ:施設>
<SG収集対象外>

name: About the armor shop
note:
<SG説明:
The selection of equipment at the armor shop is linked to the
adventurer's rank. When Clea's evaluation rises at the Adventurer's
Guild, you can purchase more powerful equipment. ①Level 01 Equipment
Purchase Rights: Provisional Junior Member ②Level 02 Equipment
Purchase Rights: Provisional Intermediate Member ③Level 03 Equipment
Purchase Rights: Provisional Senior Member ④Level 04 Equipment
Purchase Rights: Rookie Adventurer ⑤Level 05 Equipment Purchase
Rights: Skilled Adventurer ⑥Level 06 Equipment Purchase Rights:
Accomplished Adventurer ⑦Level 07 Equipment Purchase Rights: Elite
Adventurer ⑧Level 08 Equipment Purchase Rights: Seasoned Adventurer
⑨Level 09 Equipment Purchase Rights: Expert Adventurer ⑩Level 10
Equipment Purchase Rights: On Par with the Three Greats. I recommend
checking out the armor shop when your rank goes up.
>
<SG種別:3>
<SGカテゴリ:施設>
<SG収集対象外>

note:
<SG説明:
This is the home of an archaeologist located in the Fotizona region.
It offers the following services: ① Exchange of ancient coins and
items ② Selling of any remaining ancient coins after exchanging all
items. Some of the exchange items serve as prerequisites for adult
quests. Please explore the dungeons and try to collect ancient coins.
>
<SG種別:3>
<SGカテゴリ:施設>

name: About the suspicious shop
note:
<SG説明:
Mysterious shops become special hidden shops that can be accessed by
using AAA. These illegal establishments allow you to purchase high-
priced special equipment and items.  1. Nora and Relm's AAA skills are
required to enter the shop. 2. Sophia's AAA temptation is necessary to
make purchases at the shop. 3. There are two types of targeted shops:
AAA Temptation Level 2 and AAA Temptation Level 4. 4. Some items have
limited stock and purchase restrictions. It's important to note that
this is unrelated to adventurer rank. With the right skills and money,
it's possible to progress through the adventure advantageously from
the beginning.
>
<SG種別:3>
<SGカテゴリ:施設>

name: About Kasaro Bathhouse
note:
<SG説明:
This is a huge bath facility located in the Fotizona region. It offers
the following services: ① Bathing... You can use it for free and it
will fully restore your HP and MP, just like staying at an inn. ②
Massage... You can choose a character's name and use this service. It
allows you to view adult scenes. The scenes in the massage service
will vary depending on the character's lewdness level. You can check
the conditions for the variations at the reception desk. Additionally,
you can view a special illustration while bathing.
>
<SG種別:3>
<SGカテゴリ:施設>

name: About the auction venue
note:
<SG説明:
The auction facility located in the Fotizona Harbor is the venue. At
the auction venue, you can participate in auctions. ① You can
participate in the auction if you have 10,000G. ② You can check the
contents of the auction items by talking to an NPC. ③ The auction
items are random (except for some exceptions, there is no concept of
inventory). ④ The target item and starting price are announced at the
start of the auction. ⑤ If your funds do not meet the starting price,
you will automatically drop out. ⑥ There are three other players
(NPCs) besides yourself. ⑦ NPCs randomly raise the amount before you.
⑧ After the NPCs finish, it's your turn to raise the price. ⑨ Within 5
seconds, choose from "+1000G", "+100G", or "give up". ⑩ If everyone

name: Battle Strategy
note:
<SG説明:
Here are some hints on how to deal with tough enemies. When
encountering an enemy that cannot be defeated, please check the
following items:  1. Level up: Leveling up will increase your basic
stats and allow you to acquire new skills. It also grants SP, which
can be used to unlock skills in the skill tree. Clear dungeons and
repeat quests to level up.  2. Unlock skills in the skill tree: Use SP
to unlock skills in the skill tree. Many of these skills will give you
an advantage in battle, ensuring a favorable outcome. Be proactive in
unlocking them.  3. Level up skills through sexual technique
development: Some of the skills unlocked in the skill tree have
corresponding sexual techniques (hidden skills). Developing these
sexual techniques with AP will enhance the corresponding skills listed
in the table. This will greatly improve your chances in battle, so be
proactive in developing them.
>
<SG説明2:
④As you progress through the mandatory quests, you will be able to
enhance your weapons. Let's actively strengthen our weapons in order
to reap the benefits of weapon enhancement. As you progress through
the mandatory quests, you will have access to purchasable armor.
Always check if you are equipped with the latest armor. Many enemies
have set [Elemental Weaknesses] or [Abnormal Status Weaknesses]. Try
various skills to determine the enemy's weaknesses and gain an
advantage in battle. When you hit an elemental weakness, it will be
indicated as [weakness]. Conversely, if the opponent has resistance,
it will be indicated as [resistance].
>
<SG説明3:
⑦Let's make good use of buffs and debuffs. Buffs strengthen allies,
while debuffs weaken enemies. It is also possible to use buffs and
debuffs through items. ⑧Postpone it for later. It can be a strategy to
intentionally leave it alone and progress with other quests. Let's
level up and unlock skills by progressing with other quests. ⑨Utilize
the one-hit kill command. It is a last resort, but by pressing the [F9
key] on the command selection screen, you can instantly kill the
enemy. Please use it when you absolutely cannot defeat a strong enemy.
>
<SG種別:3>
<SGカテゴリ:攻略法>
<SG収集対象外>

name: Assessing Preparatory Actions
note:
<SG説明:
There are powerful enemies that have a preparatory action before using
their special moves. In such cases, the enemies will emit a red light,
so let's take measures against their special moves. There are various
ways to avoid them, such as entering a defensive state, protecting
oneself, or inflicting status ailments on the enemy. Let's skillfully
handle the enemy's special moves depending on the situation.
> 
<SGピクチャ:hint/hint_strategy>

<SGピクチャ優先度:bottom>

<SGテキスト位置:0>

name: Effective Utilization of AAA
note:
<SG説明:
AAAIn this game, you can collect items and gold. In the town and
dungeons, make sure to frequently change characters and carry out the
collection.  - Obtaining items and gold: Nora the thief has a keen
sense of smell, while Relm the magician has a talent for discovery. -
Obtaining through battles and negotiations: Clea specializes in duels,
while Sophia the priestess excels in seduction. In particular, the
shady shop that can be accessed through Sophia's seduction is
important. You can purchase items that increase SP and AP, as well as
special equipment. If you prioritize strengthening, your adventures
will definitely become easier.
> 
<SG説明2:
Clea's AAA special move is capable of defeating enemies without
engaging in battle. It is recommended to actively utilize it as you
can also obtain experience points and gold. By placing the priest
Sophia at the forefront of the battle, the amount of gold obtained
upon victory will increase. If you want to earn gold, deliberately
engaging in regular battles can also be a technique.
>

<SGカテゴリ:攻略法>

<SG種別:4>
<SGカテゴリ:引き継ぎ方法>
<SG収集対象外>

name: About the Fotizona Empire
note:
<SG説明:
Originally, it was a small city-state, but it was unified into its
current form through repeated wars and diplomacy. Within the country,
the capital of the former unified nation remains as a city and has
greatly developed. Led by the capital, Fotizona, it has seven major
cities and is supported by paved roads and constructed waterways. The
name means a place illuminated by light, a sunny place. This is rooted
in their religious beliefs, defining their own country as an
equivalent existence to the world of light, hence the name. Places
outside their country are referred to as places where light does not
reach, shadowy places, and the people living there are defined as the
people of darkness. The nation follows the myth that it was originally
one. Therefore, there is no stance of aggressive warfare, and all acts
of war are carried out as "reunification wars." Fotizona is both the
name of the empire and the capital. It is the center of politics and
religion, and has a senate formed by the royal family and influential
figures from each city. The adventurer's guild is also located in the
capital. This is also related to the fact that the adventurer's guild
was once born from the empire's reconnaissance unit.
>
<SG種別:1>
<SGカテゴリ:地名>
<SG収集対象外>

name: Fotizona Empire's capital city
note:
<SG説明:
■  Camps, the City of the Grasslands (First Annexation): A city that
bears the ancient word meaning "grasslands." It is a major
agricultural region. Once inhabited by small-scale farmers, the
difficulty of maintaining the land due to war led the farmers to sell
their land, resulting in the creation of large estates managed by
nobles. Similar to Oros, there are many slaves. In recent years, there
has been a conflict between former farmers who seek to reclaim their
land and the nobles.  Kanonas, the City of the Code (Second
Annexation): A city that bears the ancient word meaning "code." It is
home to a magic academy, and the residents of Kanonas consider
themselves the center of civilization, with Kanonas as the center of
culture. It attracts magic users and those associated with magic. The
central area of Kanonas used to be in a different location, but due to
a large-scale magical accident that caused desertification, the magic
academy was relocated to its current location.
>
<SG説明2:
■  City of Valie, the City of the Valley (Third Annexation): A city
that bears the ancient word meaning "valley." It was once a thriving
city known for its crystal mining region. However, the crystals have
now depleted, and the focus has shifted to excavating metals. Many of
the miners have migrated to Oros, and the city is no longer as lively
as it used to be. In recent years, the abandoned mining sites have
become a social problem, inhabited by thieves and beasts.  City of
Valt, the City of the Forest (Fourth Annexation): A city that bears
the ancient word meaning "forest." The majority of the region is
covered in forests. The people who originally lived here were feared
as barbarians and revered as skilled mercenaries on the battlefield.
Even after the empire's annexation, the city continued to produce
exceptional warriors and gave birth to several heroes. Additionally,
after the empire's annexation, it became a beloved hunting ground and
retreat for the nobles, with numerous villas being built.
>
<SG説明3:
■  'Oros, the City of Mountains (Fifth Annexation)'  A city that bears
the ancient word for "mountain" in its name. It used to be a
relatively inconspicuous city, but after the empire's annexation,
extensive crystal excavation took place in the area. Many mine workers
reside here, including slaves and immigrants. They are unilaterally
resented by the people of Valie, which was once the largest crystal
excavation area.  'Myukos, the City of the Harbor (Sixth Annexation)'
A city that bears the ancient word for "bay" in its name. It is
characterized by a large harbor. It was the last city to be
incorporated into the empire among the seven major cities. During the
war with the neighboring country Tarasa, soldiers marched through this
city, leading to its great prosperity. It is a melting pot of races,
and various people live here. Due to such circumstances, there are
many unique crimes, and an underworld has formed.
>
<SG種別:1>
<SGカテゴリ:地名>
<SG収集対象外>

name: Special location in the Photizona Empire
note:
<SG説明:
■  - Fotizona Royal Palace: The political center of the empire and the
residence of the successive kings. It is a beautiful building and
symbolizes the power of the empire.  - Casaro Bathhouse: A huge
bathhouse facility built by the noble Casaro in the Fotizona region to
gain entry into the Senate. It is also famous as a tourist
destination, attracting many visitors.  - Atomis Temple: A temple in
the Fotizona region where the priestesses of the Terios religion
reside. It is a very important place for the Terios religion, and
devout believers always make pilgrimages during their lifetime.  -
Pizma Arena: A massive arena built in the martial arts city of Jinami
in the Fotizona region. It was constructed by the formidable King
Pizma and bears his name as the arena's title.
>
<SG説明2:
■  Aftermath of Judgment: The remains of a great destruction that
occurred in the Kanonas region, where there used to be a magic
academy. A strange desert spreads out, and it is said to be the place
where the supreme god, Sol, passed judgment on humans who had become
arrogant.  Mount Monimos: The highest mountain in the Empire, located
in the Valie region. There is a legend of a hero who lured and
defeated a dragon living at the summit.  Prostitution Island: An
island in the Myukos region that was once used as a military base. It
has now become a huge pleasure district for the purpose of
prostitution.
>
<SG種別:1>
<SGカテゴリ:地名>
<SG収集対象外>

name: About the neighboring country Tarasa
note:
<SG説明:
Over the years, this maritime nation has been vying for hegemony with
Fotizona and the surrounding region. It is a representative presence
of the nations that feel a sense of crisis as Fotizona rapidly
expands, and it has strong support from anti-Fotizona countries. In
the First Tarasa War, they successfully defended themselves despite
suffering numerous casualties. However, in the Second Tarasa War, they
were pushed to the brink and were saved by the coincidence of the
death of Fotizona's king, Agnos. As a result, they lost several
territories and some talented magicians and researchers fled to
Fotizona.
>
<SG種別:1>
<SGカテゴリ:地名>
<SG収集対象外>

name: Unexplored Region
note:
<SG説明:
■  Paraxeno: An unexplored continent said to be inhabited by beastmen.
Multiple documents depict the appearance of beastmen, leading to the
belief that they actually exist. According to one passage, it is said
to be the destination where people born between demons and humans have
migrated.  Krypten: An unexplored continent that was said to be the
goal of the first guildmaster of the adventurer guild, Ftera, named
Pruce. Currently, it is not a specific location but a general term for
unexplored lands.
>
<SG種別:1>
<SGカテゴリ:地名>
<SG収集対象外>

name: Imperial Politics
note:
<SG説明:
■The Kingdom and the Senate are a nation governed by monarchy. The
Senate, composed of nobles who advise the king, holds a very strong
influence. The nobles who make up the Senate are the royal families
and influential figures of the former city-states, and incorporating
them into the centers of power has led to stable expansion.   ■
Exclusive to the King: The king is considered the father of the
nation, and suitable individuals have served as kings since the
founding of the country. The king is chosen and recognized by the
citizens. Therefore, hereditary succession is generally not adopted,
but in cases of the sudden death of the king or emergencies,
hereditary succession may be used to avoid political turmoil.
>
<SG説明2:
■  The King's Responsibilities The king's greatest responsibility is
the defense of the nation, as well as being the commander of the
entire army. Additionally, they are the protector of the Terios
religion, and it is highly emphasized that they serve as a model of
religious morality, not only during religious ceremonies but in all
aspects of their life. Throughout history, almost all six kings have
engaged in military expeditions. This is considered the most virtuous
act for a religious figure, as well as a means of population expansion
and the expansion of the economic sphere for self-defense.  Current
King and the Royal Family During wartime, the king passed away, and
currently, the throne is vacant. Due to the young age of the second
queen's son, the second queen is acting as regent in their place.
There is a tendency to disregard the advice of the Senate and a
growing conflict between the regent and the Senate. However, there is
also a faction supporting the second queen, and the political
situation is in turmoil. Additionally, there is a rumor circulating
that the son of the first queen has gone missing and may have been
assassinated.
>
<SG種別:1>
<SGカテゴリ:帝国の体制>
<SG収集対象外>

name: Imperial Rank
note:
<SG説明:
■  Royal Family: The king is an absolute existence and stands apart
from the rest of the royal family. The king is seen as the father of
the citizens and commands respect as the highest commander of the
military. The king's relatives are also recognized as respectable
individuals. However, even the king is not allowed to transfer power
to someone without ability or appoint them to important positions.
Noble Members of the Senate: The Senate consists of nobles from the
former city-state and influential individuals who hold significant
power. They are sometimes allowed to give instructions to the king
that are close to orders, and the nation has been maintained through a
proper balance between the king and the Senate. The Senate is expected
to be exemplary citizens and is required to make efforts in various
aspects such as participating in wars and providing funds for wars. As
a result, despite being lifelong positions, there are many casualties
and retirees in the Senate, and proper turnover has been maintained.
However, as the number of wars decreases, proper turnover no longer
occurs, and there has been a growing problem of individuals enriching
themselves through trade and the operation of large farms.
>
<SG説明2:
■  Nobles: They are the upper class of the Imperial Empire and the
elite members of society. They are the families that produce members
of the Senate and sometimes even have connections to the royal family.
In addition, it is always the nobles who are chosen as priests of the
Terios religion, and they are not chosen from the commoner class. This
is because it is believed that the nobles have a special power to
communicate with the gods. Like the Senate, they have been
participating in wars and providing funds for wars as a model for the
citizens. However, like the Senate, there has been a growing problem
of some nobles becoming wealthy through trade and running large farms.
Citizens: They are the ordinary residents of the Empire and the
commoners. They are considered to be the middle class, but there are
citizens who are closer to the nobles and those who live day by day,
so there is a wide range. They live their daily lives with various
jobs, but all men are required to serve in the military, and by
completing their military service, they become full-fledged citizens.
>
<SG説明3:
■  Immigrants: The boundary between immigrants and citizens is
determined by whether or not they have military service experience.
For males, it is required to have military service experience, while
for females, they can be treated as citizens if they become the wives
of military service veterans. Additionally, religious devotion is
highly important, and those who blaspheme against the gods are not
treated as citizens and continue to be treated as immigrants. There
are immigrants who live in the empire, but many of them are engaged in
trade-related jobs and are temporary residents in the empire. The
benefits of becoming an imperial citizen are much higher, so many
immigrants willingly become citizens.  Slaves: People who were sold
during times of war or by slave traders. Additionally, those who
commit crimes and are incarcerated can also be sold as slaves. Slaves
can be treated as literal slaves in large plantations or coal mines,
but there are also those who serve in important positions such as
tutors or secretaries and are highly valued. Generally, they are seen
as individuals who have an equal chance to become citizens, and it is
considered a crime to treat them too harshly. Furthermore, it is
prohibited to buy or sell citizens or nobles as slaves, and both the
seller and the buyer will be punished if discovered.
>
<SG種別:1>
<SGカテゴリ:帝国の体制>
<SG収集対象外>

name: Imperial Military
note:
<SG説明:
■  The military is divided into two main categories: the conscription
army, formed by the mobilization of citizens in times of need, and the
royal guard, which is responsible for maintaining the monarchy.
Citizens have an obligation to serve in the military, and the nation
maintains a certain number of standing armies. Some individuals
continue to serve in the military even after completing their
conscription, and they play an active role as professional soldiers.
During peacetime, they work as guards to maintain the security of the
nation and the city. Additionally, nobles have their own personal
guards, and joining the royal guard is considered a path to
advancement for warriors and mages.  Regarding the king and
conscription, the king is treated as the commander of all military
affairs within the empire. The king is elected by the citizens, and
all males have an obligation to serve in the military. As a result,
there is a strong connection between the king and the citizens, which
is considered one of the major factors contributing to the empire's
expansion. The king is seen as a father figure, and the soldiers are
treated as his sons.
>
<SG説明2:
■  Mercenaries There are quite a few individuals who work as
mercenaries within the empire. Compared to other countries, the number
of mercenaries is small because military service is mandatory.
Mercenaries are sometimes employed for tasks such as subjugating
monsters within the territories of nobles or serving as overseers for
large farms. Some of them are closer to thieves, and they are often
treated as a byproduct of the uncertain post-war situation.  Plains
and Seas The empire excels in disciplined group battles, particularly
on the plains. The concept of logistics and transportation is well-
established, and as the empire grows larger, it becomes capable of
overwhelming its enemies with resources. However, the empire is
inexperienced in naval warfare and lags behind neighboring countries
in that regard. Shipbuilding technology is still developing, and the
development of naval tactics and weapons for use at sea is considered
the fastest route to advancement.
>
<SG種別:1>
<SGカテゴリ:帝国の体制>
<SG収集対象外>

name: Imperial Organization
note:
<SG説明:
■Adventurer's Guild Ftera is the only adventurer organization approved
by the country, with a long-standing tradition. Originally, it
consisted of individuals who literally went on adventures, but as the
empire's territory expanded, its nature became diluted, and it has now
become an organization that deals with various problems. In the
previous war, they actively participated in and resolved immigration
and banditry issues, earning high praise from the nobility and the
Senate.   Terios Religion is an ancient authority that has existed
since the founding of the country. They are the administrators of the
religion and are considered the protectors of all the weak, such as
travelers, orphans, the sick, and immigrants. Their influence and
authority are tremendous, with religious facilities present throughout
the country and religious personnel being dispatched to various
locations. They have a history of conflict with the Magic Academy and
continue to have disagreements regarding the definition of magic and
their beliefs.
>
<SG説明2:
■The Magic Academy was once part of a religious faction, but it came
into conflict and separated from the religious faction due to
accusations of "devil worship". The Academy primarily focuses on
magical research, but it also values practical benefits and conducts
various studies including military, agriculture, architecture, and
astronomy. It is a national research institution where elites from the
empire gather.   The Imperial Intelligence Agency, Isheker, is the
empire's espionage agency. It originated from a reconnaissance unit
that was the precursor to the adventurer's guild. Its main purpose is
to investigate and eliminate forces hostile to the empire, and it
monitors dangerous individuals and organizations both domestically and
internationally. Its true nature is shrouded in mystery, and it is
said to be a group that pledges loyalty only to the one who sits on
the throne.
>
<SG種別:1>
<SGカテゴリ:帝国の体制>
<SG収集対象外>

name: Imperial Illegal Organization
note:
<SG説明:
■  Tomosu Raiders: A group of raiders that once operated in the
Fotizona region. They were in direct opposition to the adventurer
guild, Ftera, and were ultimately destroyed by Agonia, Simos, and
Storge. However, remnants of the group are still active and have not
given up on seeking revenge against the adventurer guild.  Loparo
Raiders: A group of raiders that operate primarily in the Campos
region. They are known for their rough behavior and are a nuisance to
the local guards.  Emma Thieves: A group of thieves formed by the
returning soldiers of the Second Tarasa War in the Campos region.
While they have a Robin Hood-like aspect to their activities,
targeting nobles who have seized land, their actions have escalated
and they are feared as "mad dogs" even among their peers. Nora, the
thief, belongs to this organization.
>
<SG説明2:
■  Chronos Thieves Guild: A group of thieves that operates mainly in
the Valie region. The number of members has decreased to less than
half of its heyday due to the closure of the Crystal Mine. Currently,
they are in a state where they are completely under the control of
local influential nobles.  Aspida Alliance: A group that operates
mainly in the Wald region. They are a group plotting for the
independence of the Wald Empire and are plundering legendary weapons
and crystals that are passed down in Wald. They consider the people of
the empire as enemies and are considered a dangerous group that
carries out indiscriminate attacks.  Rigas Bandit Group: A group that
operates mainly in the Wald region. Due to the efforts of the Bulk
Brigade and the adventurer guild Ftera, they are in a semi-destroyed
state and are unable to maintain the same level of power as before.
>
<SG説明3:
■  Pegaru Bandit Group: A group that operates in the Oros region. They
are based in the mountainous areas of Oros. It is rumored that they
have connections with the nobles of Oros.  Organization: A group that
operates primarily in the Myukos region. Their official name is
unknown and they are referred to as "the Organization." They have a
strong political influence over the port, distinguishing themselves
from other illegal groups. Cors, a wanderer, belongs to this
organization.  Demon Worshipers: A group that worships 74 demons.
Although they are collectively referred to as demon worshipers, each
individual worships a different demon. Additionally, there are many
cases where groups that worship the same demon are divided into
separate organizations. They are considered troublesome and are seen
as clear enemies of the empire.
>
<SG種別:1>
<SGカテゴリ:帝国の体制>
<SG収集対象外>

name: About adventurers
note:
<SG説明:
■  Definition of Adventurers: During the time when the empire was still
a small city-state, those who ventured to explore new territories were
all called adventurers. Therefore, in a broad sense, all the people of
the empire can be considered descendants of adventurers. This ideology
is deeply rooted among the citizen class, and many of them claim to be
the descendants of adventurers. Currently, the number of adventurers
in the purest sense has decreased. Adventurers in the past, in the
true sense of the word, were called explorers and were seen as
romanticists who were passionate about discovering unexplored
continents and the civilization of demons.  Children of Pioneers: A
general term for people who take on freelance requests without going
through the Adventurers Guild. Although there is no clear
organizational structure, they consistently assert that they are the
true successors of adventurers and pioneers, in opposition to the
Adventurers Guild and its values. There are three major forces (Armada
in the Barié region, Goat in the Wald region, and Cors in the Myukos
region), each with their own quality of requests and bases for their
activities. They are called freelance adventurers or wanderers.
>
<SG種別:1>
<SGカテゴリ:冒険者ギルド・フテラ>
<SG収集対象外>

name: About the Adventurer's Guild, Ftera.
note:
<SG説明:
■Adventurer's Guild Ftera has become the only organization that can
legally accept client requests. However, there are cases where those
in power widely advertise specific requests, and it is possible to
accept requests without being a member of Ftera. Since Agonia became
the current guild leader, Ftera has increased its confidentiality and
attracted more clients from the upper class. There are many who are
opposed to this stance, and there are those who have left Ftera or are
planning to establish a separate organization to oppose the guild.
The Origins of Adventurer's Guild Ftera can be traced back to its
early days as a reconnaissance unit within the military, with its main
missions being exploration and infiltration in enemy territories.
During peacetime, they also conducted investigations of domestic
crystal mines and extermination of monsters. After the annexation of
Oros, they were granted special rewards by King Falmako, which allowed
them the right to freely explore undeveloped areas within the country
during peacetime. They requested the establishment of their own
organization for exploration, which marked the beginning of
Adventurer's Guild Ftera.
>
<SG説明2:
■  The initial members of the adventurer guild, Ftera, known as the
Legendary Seven, are spoken of alongside various legends. Episodes of
domestic monster extermination are particularly popular and often told
by bards. However, many of these stories are considered to be
fictional, as the actual adventurer guild primarily focused on
exploring uncharted territories. The founder and first guild leader,
Pruce, is especially popular. His disappearance while aiming for a new
frontier only added to his legendary status.   Pruce... the first
guild leader. A person adorned with numerous legends.   Pistoshi...
the second guild leader. He laid the foundation of the guild as an
organization that accepts requests.   Kasusu... a master of
exploration who is said to have discovered numerous crystal mines in
Oros.   Hora... famous for recording his adventures and gaining fame
as a writer.   Bios... a master scout. His skills led to rumors of him
being a contract holder with demons.   Zoi... the only woman among
them. Numerous adventure tales featuring her alone have been produced.
Proposhi... a master of storytelling. It is said that he ensured the
establishment of the guild with his persuasive skills.
>
<SG説明3:
■  Current Adventurer Guild, Ftera: In the past, they actively engaged
in problem-solving and other activities in order to operate the
organization while aiming for new territories and to gain control over
exploration areas. This activity has become the main focus of Ftera.
As a result, many citizens view the Adventurer Guild not as
adventurers or explorers, but as problem solvers. Ftera operates under
a strict hierarchical system with very strict discipline. There are
three principles: "Do not betray, do not lie, do not run away," and it
is said that those who break their oath will be purged. It is rumored
that many people in positions of power have been assassinated due to
deceiving Ftera.   The Three Greats of Ftera: Refers to Guild Master
Agonia, Storge of Compassion, and Simos of the Unknown Night. The
guild is an organization built on trust, and their presence serves as
a guarantee of trustworthiness. Due to the nature of the Adventurer
Guild, they often attract resentment, and there are quite a few
individuals who specifically target the Adventurer Guild.
Additionally, while the relationship with the central imperial
authority is good, there have been some changes since the transfer of
power to Queen Caron.
>
<SG種別:1>
<SGカテゴリ:冒険者ギルド・フテラ>
<SG収集対象外>

name: About the Terios religion
note:
<SG説明:
■The religion revolves around the belief in the main god, Sol, and the
worship of three goddesses. Each goddess is closely related to the
real world's power, and people follow the same religion but offer
prayers to different gods. However, everyone prays equally to the main
god. The teachings are systematized and followed as the "Terios
Religion."   The belief is that this world is the "Shadow World
(Karko)," and there exists a perfect world called the "World of Light
(Teriose)." The importance is placed on cooperation and mutual respect
in an imperfect world. Above all, morality is highly valued, and
betrayal and immorality are considered sins. Therefore, whether one is
a royal or a prostitute, social class and status are irrelevant; what
matters is how much one values morality. Such a way of life is
depicted in the scriptures. Those who uphold the doctrine after death
are invited to the World of Light. Those who disregard the faith are
neither invited to the World of Light nor able to return to the Shadow
World, forever wandering in the realm between. People live according
to the moral teachings of the scriptures in order to be invited to the
World of Light.
>
<SG種別:1>
<SGカテゴリ:宗教>
<SG収集対象外>

name: Terios Religion Myth
note:
<SG説明:
■72In the world of shadows, which is the real world, it is said that
there were 72 demons. Each of them was a powerful demon, and humanity
was manipulated and tormented by these demons. The main god, Sol,
ordered his daughter gods to subdue the 72 demons. At first, they
cooperated, but eventually they competed for the position of the
eldest daughter and took different approaches to seal the demons.  ■
Initial Stage The three sisters, who received the command of the main
god, attempted to subdue the demons, but regardless of the
circumstances, they thought it would be inappropriate to subdue what
the main god had created, so they decided to seal the demons instead.
The first daughter god, Actina, created the characters engraved in the
grimoire, the second daughter god, Imiserinos, created the grimoire
and words for sealing, and the third daughter god, Deire, successfully
extracted the weaknesses of the demons needed for sealing through
skillful words. However, the seven cautious demons (the immortal
demon: Amedol, the time demon: Yurozone, the divination demon: Ipound,
the plague demon: Suhuran, the gluttony demon: Yuan, the regeneration
demon: Jien) did not reveal their weaknesses and issued a notice to
not interact with the three sisters or other demons.
>
<SG説明2:
■The two ancestors of humanity, the three sisters, were tasked with
sealing away demons in place of themselves and cooperating with
humans. The clan recognized by the three sisters, especially the two
brothers, made a promise to "establish the Basileia Kingdom, which
would unite the scattered tribes" as a reward for sealing the demons.
The older brother, Basileus, worked tirelessly for the construction of
the nation, while the younger brother, Subma, worked tirelessly for
the sealing of monsters. The older brother became the ancestor of the
royal family, and the younger brother became the ancestor of the
sorcerers.   ■ The Conflict of the Three Sisters After a long time,
they succeeded in sealing away 65 demons, but there were still 7
demons whose weaknesses were unknown and untouched. Moreover, these 7
demons possessed great power, and peace was not easily achieved.
Eventually, the three sisters began to clash over the future course of
action. The element of sibling rivalry also came into play, and each
of them started dealing with the demons in turn.
>
<SG説明3:
■The Failure of the Goddess of Daughters, Actina. First, the Goddess of
Daughters, Actina, led humanity in a battle against the demons.
However, unlike the immortal demons and goddesses, humanity, who can
die, was defeated by the demons. As a result, the Basilaea Kingdom
collapsed and split apart. It is said that this led to the current
state of multiple nations existing (and the division of races is also
said to have occurred during this time).   The Failure of the Goddess
of Daughters, Imiserinos, and the Proposal of the Goddess of
Daughters, Deire. After witnessing the failure of the Goddess of
Daughters, Actina, the Goddess of Daughters, Imiserinos, gave humanity
the power of the seven demons (immortality, eternal youth, foresight,
invulnerability, satiety, regeneration, mind reading) so that they
could resist the demons. As a result, humanity no longer feared the
demons and began to coexist with them, and some even bore children
with demons. As a result, an advanced civilization known as the Demon
Civilization emerged later on. Fearing the wrath of the main god, Sol,
the Goddess of Daughters, Deire, proposed that the three sisters
cooperate once again.
>
<SG説明4:
■The Birth of the Hero and Normalization. The three goddesses, Clea,
Nora, and Relm, discovered a young man guided by the goddesses Sophia,
Celis, and Piste, and designated him as the hero to defeat the demons.
The hero successfully subjugated the demons without betraying the
expectations of the three sisters. However, when the world achieved
peace and humanity attempted to coexist with the demons, they were
destroyed as a demonic civilization. Clea, the first goddess, took
away the seven powers and forced them to live as humans.   ■ Gifts
from the Goddesses. The goddesses bestowed their powers upon humanity.
Clea granted the miracle of self-enhancement. Nora granted the miracle
of healing. And Relm secretly passed on the power of magic to
humanity. As a result, humanity gained the ability to wield the powers
of miracles and imperfect magic. Magic is chanted by utilizing the
powers of the demons sealed within grimoires. Therefore, humanity
cannot wield the powers of the seven demons (immortality, eternal
youth, clairvoyance, invulnerability, satiety, regeneration, mind
reading) that were not sealed within the grimoires.
>
<SG種別:1>
<SGカテゴリ:宗教>
<SG収集対象外>

name: Terios Religious Mythology and Founding Myth
note:
<SG説明:
■The Fotizona Empire, which is an extension of the religious mythology,
finds its legitimacy as a nation within the mythology of the Terios
religion. Therefore, it is considered a nation that follows in the
footsteps of the oldest nation in the mythology, the Basileia Kingdom.
■ A nation that collapsed due to the battle with demons In the battle
against the seven powerful demons, the nation fought under the
guidance of the goddess daughter, Actina. However, humanity was
defeated by the immortal demons, and the Basileia Kingdom collapsed.
Afterward, the goddess daughter, Imiserinos, bestowed upon humanity
the powers of the seven demons (immortality, eternal youth,
clairvoyance, invulnerability, abundance, regeneration, mind reading).
However, the ancestors of the Fotizona Empire resisted this temptation
and fought as humans. After the demons were defeated by a hero, the
construction of the nation began to reunite the scattered humanity.
>
<SG説明2:
■In the era when the children of the hero descended, there were a
beautiful brother and sister. The brother, in order to maintain his
power as a king and keep his beautiful sister, who was said to be the
reincarnation of a goddess, by his side, began to borrow the power of
the demon civilization. People were killed, and the nation fell into
chaos. At such a time, on a stormy night, a hero appeared to the
imprisoned sister and had a relationship with her. Beautiful twins
were born, but the brother, angered by this, ordered the twins to be
killed. The soldier who was ordered to kill them received a revelation
saying, "These two should be kept alive," and quickly pretended to
kill them by cutting his own arm. Afterwards, the grown twins killed
their uncle, the king, and took control of the nation.   Brotherly
Duel and the Birth of a King: Brother Atomis was skilled in magic,
while his brother Agon was skilled in martial arts. They each yielded
the throne to each other. However, contrary to the twins' feelings,
separate forces were formed independently, and the nation faced the
crisis of division. Unable to bear this, the twins fought a duel for
the throne. Suddenly, a thunderstorm struck during the duel. When the
thunderstorm subsided, only the younger brother was left standing. The
younger brother became the new king. The king did not punish anyone
who sided with the older brother and granted them religious authority.
From this time on, "fratricide (sacrifice to avoid power struggles)"
became a custom.
>
<SG説明3:
■  In the birth of a new king, a beautiful priestess, it gave rise to a
new conflict. There was a clash with neighboring tribes. During that
time, the chief of the tribe gave the priestess to the king as a means
of appeasement. The priestess was a sacred being, and the men of the
tribe were furious at the chief's actions. However, the king did not
lay a hand on the priestess and even prepared an altar for her to
offer her prayers, treating her with respect. Upon witnessing the
king's attitude, the men of the tribe were impressed and followed
suit. The chief was killed, and the entire tribe was absorbed.
Furthermore, the priestess became incorporated into the Terios
religion and gained religious authority.  ■ The King and the Senate
The king was a warrior. Therefore, he made many decisions himself,
just like on the battlefield. However, as the nation expanded, it
became difficult to maintain control with only individual judgments.
The few nobles who served as advisors eventually became the Senate and
supported the king.
>
<SG説明4:
■  Conflict with the Senate As the Senate became more organized, the
authoritarian king became the target of criticism. However, the king
waged wars, achieved victory, and made the nation prosperous. The
citizens praised the king and revered him as the father of the nation.
The Senate pointed out the problems that were piling up within the
country due to the rapid expansion, but no one, including the king,
paid any attention.  The Death of the King On the day of a solar
eclipse, the king was sitting on the throne in an outdoor temple.
Suddenly, a thunderstorm struck. After the storm passed, they
hurriedly looked at the throne, but no one was there. It is said that
the king was assassinated by the Senate. The king was born on a stormy
night, lost a half of himself (his twin brother) in the thunderstorm,
and ascended to the heavens along with the thunderstorm. The bards
sang of the great king.
>
<SG種別:1>
<SGカテゴリ:宗教>
<SG収集対象外>

name: Main God of the Terios Religion
note:
<SG説明:
■  Main God: Sol The father of the three goddesses and symbol of
perfection and completeness. Depicted as a wise figure wearing a black
robe, black represents the time before dawn and signifies "beginning."
Additionally, he is symbolized by a white perfect circle, which
represents the sun. It is believed that he possesses the power to
create something out of nothing and is considered the creator of the
world, the goddesses, and even himself. Although he created a perfect
world, the "shadow" of reality, known as "Carco," was born. Unlike the
perfect world, the reality is an imperfect world where all desires
swirl. After death, if one does not forget their reverence for the
main god and is recognized by one of the goddesses, their soul will be
invited to the perfect world, "Terios." Furthermore, while everyone
worships the main god equally, he is particularly revered by the royal
and noble families.
>
<SG説明2:
The supreme god, Sol, created three daughters to rule over the real
world, which is the world of shadows. Each of them has a distinct flaw
unlike the supreme god. This serves to highlight the perfection of the
supreme god Sol and also serves as a reminder that it is right for
those with different positions to unite. There are no clear rules
regarding the hierarchy of the goddesses, and their positions vary
depending on the goddess they are worshipped by. Therefore,
conversations about the sisters' hierarchy are considered very
delicate.
>
<SG種別:1>
<SGカテゴリ:宗教>
<SG収集対象外>

name: Daughter Goddess of Terios Religion
note:
<SG説明:
■Goddess Daughter 1: Actina, a woman clad in platinum armor with a
sword in her right hand. She is said to govern justice, law, and war.
Her mouth is covered by a large gag, rendering her unable to speak.
This is considered a symbol of expressing oneself through actions
rather than words. She is symbolized by a star shape, representing the
North Star. Actina is revered by those involved in the judiciary and
warriors. It is common to invoke her name when making an unbreakable
oath. It is said that she decapitates those who break their promises.
In some regions, she is said to have a wolf as her familiar.
>
<SG説明2:
■Daughter Goddess 2: Imiserinos A woman dressed in a gray dress, bound
all over her body. She is said to govern devotion, art, and
intelligence. Because she is completely bound, she is unable to act on
her own. This is considered a symbol of trust in others and the
granting of power. She is often depicted with a book as a symbol of
intelligence. She is symbolized by a crescent moon, representing
imperfection. She is primarily worshipped by priests and wizards. She
is also seen as the ideal image of a woman, as she has given birth to
heroes. In wedding ceremonies, it is common to pledge eternity to her.
In some regions, she is said to have a pigeon as her familiar.
>
<SG説明3:
■Daughter Goddess 3: Deirei A woman dressed in black clothing, with a
white eyepatch over her left eye. It is said that her left side
represents cunning and deceit, while her right side represents
business and negotiation. The covered eye and the normal eye symbolize
duality, representing good and evil, beauty and ugliness. She is
symbolized by the planet Venus and is said to embody duality from the
morning star to the evening star. She is primarily worshipped by
underground figures such as thieves and prostitutes. She is also
popular among merchants due to episodes involving secretly sharing
magic with humans and negotiating with demons. She is known as a
goddess with a somewhat unique position due to her duality. In some
regions, it is said that she uses snakes as familiars.
>
<SG種別:1>
<SGカテゴリ:宗教>
<SG収集対象外>

name: Terios Church's Demon
note:
<SG説明:
■According to legend, there were 72 demons in existence. Out of those,
65 were sealed in grimoires by the founder of magic, Subma. The
remaining 7 demons were directly defeated by heroes as they couldn't
be sealed. Humanity is able to invoke magic spells by harnessing the
power of the sealed demons.   ■The 7 Demons: - Immortal Demon: Amedol
- Time Demon: Yurozone - Divination Demon: Ipound - Plague Demon:
Suhuran - Gluttony Demon: Yuan - Regeneration Demon: Jien
>
<SG説明2:
■  The Demon Civilization refers to the civilization that was created
during the era when demons and humans coexisted. It is considered a
time when humans had the highest abilities, and various technologies
and buildings were born in a short period of time. However, after the
subjugation of demons, that civilization was erased and many
technologies disappeared. Some of them still exist as weapons and
artifacts, and they are recognized as demon weapons and oparts.
Regarding the belief in demons, it is prohibited to worship demons
themselves. Grimoires are considered symbols of the miracles of gods
and heroes who sealed demons and become objects of worship. However,
some nobles, merchants, and clans of magicians have adopted demons as
their crests, and they have a strong popularity as symbols of power.
The stories of sealed demons and wise men are popular even among
minstrels, and they are generally widely accepted. Conservative
factions are conducting activities against such demon worship.
>
<SG種別:1>
<SGカテゴリ:宗教>
<SG収集対象外>

name: About Dragons
note:
<SG説明:
■Dragons, the symbol of demons. Dragons are treated as symbols of
demons. In reality, not all demons have the appearance of dragons, but
the image of demons being dragons has become established. This is
believed to be influenced by the songs and paintings of minstrels.
Dragons are purely mythical creatures that appear in mythology, and
there are no creatures like dragons in the current empire. Dragons are
purely legendary, imaginary creatures, and there are no citizens who
believe in their existence.
>
<SG説明2:
■Dragons in this world are treated as symbols of power and fame. There
are widespread anecdotes such as "The legendary founder defeated a
dragon and established a country" and "The nobility who are
descendants of dragons." In the empire, there is an honorable title
called Dragon Slayer, which has been awarded only to a limited number
of individuals who have saved the nation from crisis. Dragons are
regarded as symbols of strength and can be used by powerful
individuals regardless of good or evil. For example, anonymous clients
(powerful individuals who need to conceal their names) may use the
name "Dragon" for their requests, or illegitimate children of powerful
individuals may be referred to as "Dragons."
>
<SG種別:1>
<SGカテゴリ:宗教>
<SG収集対象外>

name: About Miracles
note:
<SG説明:
■  Regarding the broad definition of miracles, in religious
interpretation, miracles are considered to be faith, prayer, and
existence. Everything created by the supreme god Sol is considered a
miracle, and those who live according to the holy scriptures are said
to embody miracles themselves.  Regarding the narrow definition of
miracles, generally, miracles refer to the power wielded by monks and
similar individuals to bring about healing, strengthening, exorcism,
and recovery. Magic is considered to be the counterpart of miracles,
and it is a power derived from the demon-sealing grimoire, while
miracles are believed to be bestowed by the goddesses.
>
<SG説明2:
■The Terios Church and the Magic Academy were originally part of the
same organization, but it is said that they split due to different
interpretations of miracles and magic. For the Terios Church, magic is
seen as the "product of miracles that seal demons," and they interpret
demons and magic as something not to be praised. They view excessive
reliance on magic as a sign of corruption and succumbing to the
temptation of demons.  ■ The Hero as a Symbol of Miracles The hero is
an existence born from the collaboration of the goddesses, and is
treated as a symbol of miracles. There are numerous episodes of saints
representing religions and heroes, and the hero is spoken of as a
representative of the goddesses and a symbol of miracles. It is also
believed that humans were bestowed with the power of miracles from the
goddesses through a white dove, and within the empire, there is a
custom of cherishing doves as special creatures, including religious
dignitaries. Additionally, white doves are often depicted in religious
buildings and reliefs.
>
<SG種別:1>
<SGカテゴリ:宗教>
<SG収集対象外>

name: About the Magic Academy
note:
<SG説明:
■  About the Magic Academy: A research institution that conducts
studies on magic. Initially, it was part of a religious faction, but
it came into conflict and separated from the religious faction due to
accusations of "devil worship." The ideological influence remained
with the religious faction, while the practical influence shifted to
the Academy. Currently, various studies, including magic, are being
conducted, and it is viewed as a national research institution for
agriculture, military, architecture, and other fields. The
organization's internal structure is bureaucratic due to dealing with
advanced and dangerous information, and strict information management
is enforced.  About the Archmage: The highest authority figure in the
Magic Academy. They are considered a separate entity from the secular
world (including the initial strong religious connotations), and their
name is lost, with only their position being referred to. The Archmage
is the symbolic figure of the merit-based Magic Academy, where the
individual with the highest knowledge and skill in magic is appointed
to the position. It is customary for the Archmages of the past to be
referred to as "(Name of Achievement) Archmage" based on their major
accomplishments after their death.
>
<SG説明2:
■The Magic Academy's hierarchy is divided into three levels: Archmage
at the top, followed by High Mage, Intermediate Mage, and Low Mage. It
is an organizational structure that evaluates research achievements,
and those who have made effective inventions or discoveries can move
up in rank. Age, gender, and years of affiliation are not considered;
only pure ability is taken into account. Additionally, there are
individuals with deep knowledge of magic who are enrolled in the Magic
Academy, even if they do not possess the talent for casting spells,
and they are referred to as researchers. However, currently, the terms
"magician," "mage," and "researcher" are used based on personal
preference, and there are no strict boundaries between their names.  ■
Blemish of the Magic Academy: During the time when Kanonas maintained
its independence, a catastrophic event called the Judgment of Sol
occurred, resulting in massive destruction. The organization that
became the predecessor of the Magic Academy was disbanded, and the
entire region turned into a desert. From the perspective of the Terios
religion, it is referred to as the "end result of devil worship,"
while the Magic Academy describes it as a "magic accident." Despite
being a direct event of Kanonas being annexed by Fotizona, the details
of what actually happened remain a mystery.
>
<SG種別:1>
<SGカテゴリ:魔法>
<SG収集対象外>

name: About Magic
note:
<SG説明:
■  About Magic: Magic is said to be possible through the use of the
power of demons sealed in grimoires (demons are sealed in a space
called "Acri" at the entrance of the grimoire). Magicians often refer
to themselves as "the Achievers of the Three Unsealings," which means
they perform incantations by deciphering and understanding the magic
circles written in the grimoires. Grimoire research is mostly
conducted under the direction of the state, with a few exceptions. The
original grimoires can only be accessed and analyzed by the elites of
the Magic Academy.  Magicians: Magicians are considered "readers of
books" who can understand the formulas in grimoires. While they may be
able to cast basic magic spells, most of them can only perform
incantations as magic after acquiring specialized knowledge. With few
exceptions, magicians are researchers, and only a few of them venture
out on their own adventures. Their goal is to advance in the academy
or become the personal mage of royalty or nobility.
>
<SG説明2:
■The Lost Grimoires (Lost Magic) There are said to be 65 grimoires that
have sealed away demons, and their whereabouts are constantly being
investigated by the Academy. Some of them have disappeared during
research, while others are said to have been killed by demons or
driven mad by reading the grimoires. Currently, the Academy is said to
be managing the original copies of over 40 grimoires. ■ The Grimoires
Lost Forever These are related to the legend of the hero, and it is
said that the seven demons (immortality, eternal youth, clairvoyance,
invulnerability, satiety, regeneration, mind reading) that were not
sealed in the grimoires were defeated by the hero. Therefore, the
grimoires that cannot be found are referred to as "the grimoires lost
forever." ■ The Blank Grimoire This is a grimoire said to have been
created by the ancestor of the wizards, Subma, borrowing the power of
the goddesses. It is a special grimoire with the power to seal away
demons, and it is said to have sealed away everything except the seven
demons defeated by the hero. The manufacturing method of the blank
grimoire is considered top secret within the Academy, and not only its
production but also research on it is prohibited.

>
<SG種別:1>
<SGカテゴリ:魔法>
<SG収集対象外>
